  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\nWhen attempting to use the `eth_syncing` rpc method to determine if the node is synced or not, it returns `false` even though it is not in sync\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. Run `eth_blockNumber` against local node and reference node\r\n2. Observe local node is behind reference node\r\n3. Run `eth_syncing` against local node\r\n4. Observe `false` returned implying node is synced\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n`eth_syncing` to return block sync data when not fully synced and only return false when synced.\r\n\r\n**Screenshots**\r\n```\r\n/usr/local/bin # curl -d '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"method\":\"eth_blockNumber\",\"params\":[]}' -H \"Content-Type:application/json\" http://localhost:8545\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"result\":\"0x2e4e7e6\"}\r\n/usr/local/bin # curl -d '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"method\":\"eth_blockNumber\",\"params\":[]}' -H \"Content-Type:application/json\" https://mainnet.optimism.io\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"result\":\"0x2e4ed7c\",\"id\":1}\r\n/usr/local/bin # curl -d '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"method\":\"eth_syncing\",\"params\":[]}' -H \"Content-Type:application/json\" http://localhost:8545\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"result\":false}\r\n/usr/local/bin # curl -d '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"method\":\"eth_syncing\",\"params\":[]}' -H \"Content-Type:application/json\" https://mainnet.optimism.io\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"result\":false,\"id\":1}\r\n```\r\n\r\n**System Specs:**\r\n - OS: Alpine Linux v3.15\r\n - Package Version (or commit hash): Geth/v1.9.10-stable/linux-amd64/go1.18\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nl2geth syncing against l1",
